  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>New Delhi: Corporate hospital chain, <a href=\"/tag/global+health+limited\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Global Health Limited</a>, \"Medanta, has announced plans to lease a 80 bedded cancer hospital in Indore, Madhya Pradesh. Under the Business Transfer Agreement (BTA), Medanta will pay a consideration of Rs 30 crores for the transfer of business, including the assignment of the long-term lease. The new hospital is located within 500 meters from Medanta’s existing 175-bedded multi-specialty facility and expects the deal to drive operational synergies, optimise capacity utilisation, and improve patient flow across both facilities. </p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>At its new facility, Medanta plans to launch a comprehensive oncology program, to expand its specialty services in Indore. </p>\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>“With state-of-the-art oncology infrastructure, this facility enables us to add comprehensive cancer care, a previously missing specialty while further expanding our existing range of services,” said Pankaj Sahni, Group CEO, Medanta. </p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>“The hospital complements our Indore campus, enhancing patient access and creating operational synergies across the two facilities,” he added.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                              